</subtitle><author><name>Dede Dindin Qudsy</name><email>xtrymind@gmail.com</email><uri>http://xtrymind.github.io/</uri></author><entry><title type="html">Hide windows partitions</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/2017/03/22/hide-windows-partition.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Hide windows partitions" /><published>2017-03-22T10:53:00+07:00</published><updated>2017-03-22T10:53:00+07:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/2017/03/22/hide%20windows%20partition</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/2017/03/22/hide-windows-partition.html">&lt;p&gt;create &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;/etc/udev/rules.d/99-hide-ntfs-partitions.rules&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;KERNEL&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;==&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;sda4&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, ENV&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;UDISKS_IGNORE&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;}=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;1&quot;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;which &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;sda4&lt;/code&gt; is windows partition you want to hide&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;sudo udevadm trigger &lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;</content><author><name>Dede Dindin Qudsy</name><email>xtrymind@gmail.com</email><uri>http://xtrymind.github.io/</uri></author><summary type="html">create /etc/udev/rules.d/99-hide-ntfs-partitions.rules KERNEL==&quot;sda4&quot;, ENV{UDISKS_IGNORE}=&quot;1&quot;</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Install Flashtool on Arch Linux</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/2017/03/22/Install-Flashtool-on-Arch-Linux.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Install Flashtool on Arch Linux" /><published>2017-03-22T10:37:00+07:00</published><updated>2017-03-22T10:37:00+07:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/2017/03/22/Install%20Flashtool%20on%20Arch%20Linux</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/2017/03/22/Install-Flashtool-on-Arch-Linux.html">&lt;h4 id=&quot;aur&quot;&gt;Aur&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;clone aur &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;git clone https://aur.archlinux.org/xperia-flashtool.git&lt;/code&gt; (flaged out of date)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;$ cd xperia-flashtool
$ makepkg -si
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;manual&quot;&gt;Manual&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Download Flashtool for linux at &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.flashtool.net/downloads_linux.php&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;unzip using command&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;7z x flashtool-0.9.23.1-linux.tar.7z &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; tar -xvf flashtool-0.9.23.1-linux.tar&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;create &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;/etc/udev/rules.d/63-sonyxperia.rules&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;SUBSYSTEM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;==&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;usb&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;ACTION&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;==&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;add&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, SYSFS&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;idVendor&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;}==&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;0fce&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, SYSFS&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;idProduct&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;}==&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;*&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;MODE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;0777&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And then just cd to flashtool directory and start with sudo ./Flashtool&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://xtrymind.files.wordpress.com/2017/03/screenshot-from-2017-03-10-07-29-50.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;alignnone size-full wp-image-630&quot; src=&quot;https://xtrymind.files.wordpress.com/2017/03/screenshot-from-2017-03-10-07-29-50.png&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;739&quot; height=&quot;415&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Dede Dindin Qudsy</name><email>xtrymind@gmail.com</email><uri>http://xtrymind.github.io/</uri></author><summary type="html">Aur clone aur git clone https://aur.archlinux.org/xperia-flashtool.git (flaged out of date) $ cd xperia-flashtool $ makepkg -si Manual Download Flashtool for linux at here</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Enable tap-to-click</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/2017/03/22/Enable-tap-to-click.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Enable tap-to-click" /><published>2017-03-22T09:30:26+07:00</published><updated>2017-03-22T09:30:26+07:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/2017/03/22/Enable%20tap-to-click</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/2017/03/22/Enable-tap-to-click.html">&lt;p&gt;install libinput because xf86-input-synaptics ( based on Arch Wiki ) is in maintenance mode and is no longer updated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;sudo pacman -S libinput xf86-input-libinput&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;add &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;30-touchpad.conf&lt;/code&gt; to &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;/etc/X11/xorg.conf.d/:&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;Section &quot;InputClass&quot;
       Identifier &quot;tap-by-default&quot;
       MatchIsTouchpad &quot;on&quot;
       MatchDriver &quot;libinput&quot;
       Option &quot;Tapping&quot; &quot;on&quot;
EndSection
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To enable it in current session without restart:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;libinput-list-devices  
 &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;xinput list-props &lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;your touchpad devices&quot;&lt;/span&gt;  
 &lt;span class=&quot;c&quot;&gt;# Enable tap-click  &lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;xinput &lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;set&lt;/span&gt;-prop &lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;your touchpad devices&quot;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;libinput Tapping Enabled&quot;&lt;/span&gt; 1&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;</content><author><name>Dede Dindin Qudsy</name><email>xtrymind@gmail.com</email><uri>http://xtrymind.github.io/</uri></author><summary type="html">install libinput because xf86-input-synaptics ( based on Arch Wiki ) is in maintenance mode and is no longer updated. $ sudo pacman -S libinput xf86-input-libinput</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Welcome to Jekyll!</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/jekyll/update/2017/03/22/welcome-to-jekyll.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Welcome to Jekyll!" /><published>2017-03-22T07:47:07+07:00</published><updated>2017-03-22T07:47:07+07:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/jekyll/update/2017/03/22/welcome-to-jekyll</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/jekyll/update/2017/03/22/welcome-to-jekyll.html">&lt;p&gt;You’ll find this post in your &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;_posts&lt;/code&gt; directory. Go ahead and edit it and re-build the site to see your changes. You can rebuild the site in many different ways, but the most common way is to run &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;jekyll serve&lt;/code&gt;, which launches a web server and auto-regenerates your site when a file is updated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To add new posts, simply add a file in the &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;_posts&lt;/code&gt; directory that follows the convention &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;YYYY-MM-DD-name-of-post.ext&lt;/code&gt; and includes the necessary front matter. Take a look at the source for this post to get an idea about how it works.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Jekyll also offers powerful support for code snippets:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-ruby&quot; data-lang=&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nf&quot;&gt;print_hi&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;puts&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;Hi, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;si&quot;&gt;#{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;si&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;print_hi&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;'Tom'&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;c1&quot;&gt;#=&amp;gt; prints 'Hi, Tom' to STDOUT.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Check out the &lt;a href=&quot;https://jekyllrb.com/docs/home&quot;&gt;Jekyll docs&lt;/a&gt; for more info on how to get the most out of Jekyll. File all bugs/feature requests at &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/jekyll/jekyll&quot;&gt;Jekyll’s GitHub repo&lt;/a&gt;. If you have questions, you can ask them on &lt;a href=&quot;https://talk.jekyllrb.com/&quot;&gt;Jekyll Talk&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Dede Dindin Qudsy</name><email>xtrymind@gmail.com</email><uri>http://xtrymind.github.io/</uri></author><summary type="html">You’ll find this post in your _posts directory. Go ahead and edit it and re-build the site to see your changes. You can rebuild the site in many different ways, but the most common way is to run jekyll serve, which launches a web server and auto-regenerates your site when a file is updated.</summary></entry></feed>